<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFShefrin2002">Shefrin, Hersh (2002). <i>Beyond Greed and Fear: Understanding behavioral finance and the psychology of investing</i>. New York: Oxford University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0195161211" class="internal">ISBN 0195161211</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Beyond+Greed+and+Fear%3A+Understanding+behavioral+finance+and+the+psychology+of+investing&amp;rft.aulast=Shefrin&amp;rft.aufirst=Hersh&amp;rft.au=Shefrin%2C+Hersh&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0195161211&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Behavioral_economics"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFShleifer1999">Shleifer, Andrei (1999). <i>Inefficient Markets: An Introduction to Behavioral Finance</i>. New York: Oxford University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0198292287" class="internal">ISBN 0198292287</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Inefficient+Markets%3A+An+Introduction+to+Behavioral+Finance&amp;rft.aulast=Shleifer&amp;rft.aufirst=Andrei&amp;rft.au=Shleifer%2C+Andrei&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0198292287&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Behavioral_economics"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Herbert_Simon" title="Herbert Simon">Simon, Herbert A.</a> (1987). "behavioural economics," <i><a href="/wiki/The_New_Palgrave:_A_Dictionary_of_Economics" title="The New Palgrave: A Dictionary of Economics">The New Palgrave: A Dictionary of Economics</a></i>, v. 1, pp. 221–24.</li>
</ul>
